[4] Cholera - Angola
Date: Wed, 21 Jun 2006
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2006_06_21a/en/index.html>

As of 19 Jun 2006, Angola has reported a total of 46 758 cases
including 1893 deaths with an overall (case fatality rate, CFR 4.0
percent). 14 out of 18 provinces are affected; of all cases, 49
percent have occurred in Luanda and 17 percent in Benguela provinces.
The CFR, broken down by province, ranges between 1 and 30 percent.
Although current trends show a decline in most provinces, a daily
incidence of around 125 cases is still being reported. [Epicurve with
weekly incidence in original URL. - Mod.LL] The trend to decline
continues to be observed in the provinces of Kwanza Norte, Bengo,
Malange, and Luanda. The provinces with higher daily incidence are
Luanda (42 percent) and Namibe (16 percent).
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It is interesting that the 2 provinces with increased daily
incidence are Luanda where the outbreak started and Namibe, one of
the last (so far) to be affected.
A map of Angola showing the provinces can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf> - Mod.LL]
