[6] Cholera - India (Tamil Nadu)
Date: Sat, 17 Jun 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Hindu [edited]
<http://www.thehindu.com/2006/06/17/stories/2006061716890100.htm>

Health authorities suspect outbreak of cholera in Kottivakkam kuppam
on the southern periphery of Chennai.
In the last 24 hours, 17 persons from 3 streets of the village were
admitted to the Communicable Diseases Hospital (CDH) at Tondiarpet
with symptoms of acute diarrheal disorder. Doctors said the patients
were under observation and the laboratory results would be available.
Chennai Corporation officials, meanwhile, said no cases were reported
within the city limits. On an average, 3 to 5 cases of acute
diarrheal disorder were being admitted every day from the
Corporation's Tondiarpet and Basin ties suspect outbreak of cholera
in Kottivakkam kuppam on the southern periphery.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
